
[1]zero

   ZERO, n. Cipher; nothing. The point of a thermometer from which it is
   graduated. Zero, in the thermometers of Celsius and Reaumur, is at the
   point at which water congeals. The zero of Fahrenheits thermometer is
   fixed at the point at which the mercury stands when immersed in a
   mixture of snow and common salt. In Wedgewoods pyrometer, the zero
   corresponds with 1077 degrees on Fahrenheits scale.
